bib.title: Elastic and inelastic scattering of identical heavy ions.

free_txt: The EN and MP tandem Van de Graff
generators.
Two position sensitive detectors were positioned in
most of the runs 5 cm away from the target and covered
the angles between 18 and 75 degr.
Angular distributions of the 28Si+28Si scattering could
be absolutely reproduced within 10% uncertainty
whereas variations of less than 5% were found in the
relative intensities at different angles. Much lager
deviations were observed in the case of the inelastic
24Mg+24Mg scattering where an energy resolution of
only 800 keV was obtained. The errors in determining
the scattering angles were smaller than =-1 degr. For
12C+12C and 24Mg+24Mg absolute cross sections errors
were smaller than 20% in most of the measurements.
Digitizing error
The EN and MP tandem Van de Graff
generators.
Corrections due to the change of the solid angle of
the position-sensitive detector with scattering angle
were taken into account.
The uncertainties in the absolute cross sections were
estimated to be 10% for a scattering angle of 90 degr.
This estimate is based on the accuracy of the
normalization procedure between the different runs and
the uncertainties in setting windows in the mass
spectra. The c.m. angles could be determined from the
measured energies with an accuracy of 2 degr.
